of clinicians, researchers, consumers,

115
00:05:14.215 --> 00:05:17.155
and others that allows us to dedicate the time necessary

116
00:05:17.415 --> 00:05:20.595
to develop comprehensive well thought out solutions

117
00:05:20.855 --> 00:05:22.555
to the challenges being faced in cancer.

118
00:05:24.925 --> 00:05:27.225
As the Minister of Health's chief Advisor on Cancer,

119
00:05:27.725 --> 00:05:30.785
we bring a sharp focus lens to issues as they emerge,

120
00:05:31.475 --> 00:05:34.705
while also scanning the horizon to implement changes

121
00:05:35.055 --> 00:05:37.065
that will deliver results in the year ahead.

122
00:05:38.265 --> 00:05:40.845
One example of this is the work we completed recently

123
