and Taranaki opening this year

206
00:09:30.835 --> 00:09:34.935
and next with others to follow elsewhere across the MO too.

207
00:09:35.835 --> 00:09:37.425
Those are wins we should celebrate,

208
00:09:38.395 --> 00:09:40.335
but there is much work left to do.

209
00:09:43.035 --> 00:09:44.285
That improvement in survival

210
00:09:44.285 --> 00:09:46.205
that I talked about is not happening as quickly

211
00:09:46.385 --> 00:09:47.445
as NPR countries.

212
00:09:47.865 --> 00:09:50.365
We are falling behind our international comparators

213
00:09:51.395 --> 00:09:52.405
incidence rates.

214
00:09:52.825 --> 00:09:55.405
So the, the risk of getting cancer has been dropping

215
00:09:55.465 --> 00:09:58.205
for decades due to steady reductions in smoking rates,

216
00:09:58.825 --> 00:10:01.965
but have begun to bounce up recently, likely driven

217
00:10:02.065 --> 00:10:05.725
by increases in other risk factors like unhealthy nutrition,

218
00:10:06.205 --> 00:10:08.325
physical inactivity, and excess body weight.

219
00:10:10.265 --> 00:10:12.685
As shown in our recent through to diagnosis report,

220
00:10:13.565 --> 00:10:15.625
too many QE are getting their diagnosis

221
00:10:15.965 --> 00:10:18.105
of cancer in the emergency department

