00:10:18.405 --> 00:10:20.025
or through an acute hospital admission

223
00:10:20.855 --> 00:10:22.265
when their symptoms are advanced

224
00:10:23.045 --> 00:10:25.065
rather than early in primary care

225
00:10:25.065 --> 00:10:26.785
with their GP when their cancer is

226
00:10:26.785 --> 00:10:27.825
more likely to be curable.

227
00:10:29.515 --> 00:10:32.425
Recruiting and retaining cancer clinicians remains a

228
00:10:32.425 --> 00:10:34.705
challenge due to internationally competitive market

229
00:10:35.255 --> 00:10:37.625
with workforce shortages in a number of number

230
00:10:37.625 --> 00:10:41.185
of areas like stem cell transplant, radiology,

231
00:10:41.815 --> 00:10:45.745
radiation oncology, gynecological surgery, endoscopy,

232
00:10:45.765 --> 00:10:48.785
and others contributing to reduced access

233
00:10:48.885 --> 00:10:51.305
and increased wait times for many patients.

234
00:10:51.325 --> 00:10:55.665
And fa while investments in expanded

235
00:10:55.675 --> 00:10:56.705
navigation services

236
00:10:56.765 --> 00:11:00.585
for Maori are making a positive difference, gaps persist,

237
00:11:01.695 --> 00:11:04.625
notable among them are significant deficits in the National

238
00:11:04.725 --> 00:11:06.145
Travel Assistance Program,

239
00:11:06.555 --> 00:11:09.585
which is still falling short of meeting needs.

240
00:11:10.105 --> 00:11:13.465
Although reforms are in progress, there continue

241
00:11:13.465 --> 00:11:15.905
to be significant gaps in the quality of our data systems

242
00:11:16.685 --> 00:11:18.345
and our ability to conduct clinical

